The paper discusses the process of problem formulation in data science, which involves various actors and activities. It also highlights the importance of normative considerations in problem formulation for ensuring fairness in data science projects. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.CY (Computers and Society), which deals with the social and ethical aspects of computing. Other likely sub-categories include cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper touches upon issues related to security, network analysis, machine learning, and human-computer interaction in the context of data science problem formulation.
